                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-06-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports a rapid reduction of the military forces of the powers in
                    consequence of the acceptance by the Emperor of China of the amount of the
                    indemnity at 450,000,000 taels and the rate of interest at 4 per cent. The
                    German forces will be reduced to one brigade, and Count Waldersee has received
                    orders to return immediately to Germany).</p>
            </div>
